00:01:47,434 --> 00:01:51,827

3
00:01:51,827 --> 00:01:54,444

4
00:01:58,594 --> 00:02:05,484

5
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:31,900
By chance, do you know what time it is right now?

6
00:02:36,777 --> 00:02:38,550
Then, do you know...

7
00:02:38,550 --> 00:02:42,030
what it feels like waiting for someone who went out to see the murderer alone at night?

8
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:44,750
You said you'd see his face, but you've been gone for over three hours!

9
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:47,050
Wow, what is this?

10
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:51,500
I thought maybe you got hurt like last time while following him.

11
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,920
Are you hurt?

12
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,610
No.

13
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:58,290
It's not like I can call the police or go out myself!

14
00:02:58,290 --> 00:03:01,490
I can't even make a phone call in this damn year of 1987!

15
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:03,690
I thought I was going crazy!

16
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:05,820
Oh, I'm sorry.

17
00:03:13,570 --> 00:03:16,150
Did the man with the blue cap show up?

18
00:03:18,730 --> 00:03:20,490
Yes.

19
00:03:25,260 --> 00:03:27,410
Who was it?

20
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:33,370

21
00:03:33,370 --> 00:03:36,917

22
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:09,910
 Your father.

23
00:04:09,910 --> 00:04:12,090
 Baek Hee Seop.

24
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:18,360
This is nuts.

25
00:04:20,450 --> 00:04:23,520

26
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:33,690
 May 14th, 1987.

27
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:37,340
 Two days before the first murder takes place,

28
00:04:37,340 --> 00:04:42,510
 the person who met the victim, Lee Joo Young, was her dad?

29
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:49,450
 No, it can't be. If the one with the blue cap really is the suspect,

30
00:04:50,150 --> 00:04:56,010
 then it means he killed her mom and his own wife.

31
00:05:04,990 --> 00:05:07,140
And then, me.

32
00:05:20,770 --> 00:05:23,360
 I can't overthink it.

33
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:27,020
 I have to think calmly and level-headedly.

34
00:05:27,020 --> 00:05:29,210
 Let me get this straight.

35
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:40,650
 According to how things were, Lee Joo Young arrived seven minutes earlier.

36
00:05:40,650 --> 00:05:42,720
 If it was how things should have been,

37
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:46,120
 I was planning to go to the cafe after school tonight.

38
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:50,960
I wanted to drink coffee by myself and finish reading my book.

39
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:55,600
I really didn't have any plans to meet anyone.

40
00:05:58,820 --> 00:06:03,110
 But she ran into someone she wasn't planning to meet.

41
00:06:06,487 --> 00:06:09,800
 The guy with the blue cap. Baek Hee Seop.

42
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:16,020
 Whatever the reason may be, an argument started between the two.

43
00:06:16,020 --> 00:06:20,010
 There was someone who saw the incident at the same time.

44
00:06:20,010 --> 00:06:22,680
 Bong Bong Cafe's owner...

45
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:30,170
 Where did she go?

46
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:32,190
Hi, there!

47
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:40,920
There were other people.

48
00:06:41,690 --> 00:06:44,510
- Oh, you came. 
 - Sorry, sorry.

49
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:48,860
I heard a crazy rumor, which is why I'm a little late.

50
00:06:49,810 --> 00:06:53,860
You know how the whole school flipped out this morning because of that student teacher?

51
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:55,890
Do you know why?

52
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:58,270
Turns out...

53
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:03,630
she's a commie!

54
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:08,030
Don't you watch the news?

55
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:11,570
The college students' crazy demonstrations!

56
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:16,530
Even that weird song she sang at the picnic last time

57
00:07:16,530 --> 00:07:18,410
is the kind of song they sing in places like that.

58
00:07:18,410 --> 00:07:22,320
She was probably trying to brainwash us, too.

59
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:26,430
Isn't that so creepy?

60
00:07:27,230 --> 00:07:30,210
- Yeah, it's creepy. 
 - Right?

61
00:07:30,210 --> 00:07:34,490
Wow, it's really mind-boggling.

62
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:37,050
Even my mom and dad were saying...

63
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:42,160
How can a friend do something like this?

64
00:07:49,780 --> 00:07:52,100
How did you know?

65
00:08:15,850 --> 00:08:20,950
I wondered why I never smelled anything whenever you took a dump.

66
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:26,490
 Yoo Beom Ryong! Are you done yet?

67
00:08:26,490 --> 00:08:29,390
 Y-Yeah!

68
00:08:29,390 --> 00:08:31,720
 It's a bigger load today.

69
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:35,950
 Hey, I don't know what's happening, but there's a commotion at school.

70
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:40,510
 There are a bunch of cops looking for the student teacher.

71
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:43,500
 - Who are they looking for? 
 - The student teacher.

72
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:48,280
 Oh, geez. That guy.

73
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:56,580
 That punk didn't even flush. That dirty guy!

74
00:09:05,207 --> 00:09:06,487

75
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:30,140
That belongs to the student teacher, right?

76
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:32,590
Did you steal it?

77
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:35,620
Are you going to tell?

78
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,610
What?

79
00:09:39,610 --> 00:09:41,960
About this...

80
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:45,890
Are you going to tell anyone?

81
00:09:46,830 --> 00:09:49,130
So did you do this knowing it was wrong?

82
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:51,910
Stealing from someone and hiding it in the bathroom corner...

83
00:09:51,910 --> 00:09:54,370
Hey, if Soon Ae found out you do this kind of thing...

84
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:56,310
Soon Ae?

85
00:09:57,950 --> 00:10:01,100
How do you know my girlfriend's name?

86
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:04,060
So what if I do!

87
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:07,850
Have you thought about how hurt she will be?

88
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:19,070
You shouldn't do anything shameful to the person you like.

89
00:10:19,070 --> 00:10:22,010
That's the basic rule for guys.

90
00:10:32,597 --> 00:10:33,397

91
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,970
Wait! Wait a minute!

92
00:10:34,970 --> 00:10:36,310
Hee Seop!

93
00:10:36,310 --> 00:10:38,480
Wait! Wait!

94
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:43,260
All right. All right.

95
00:10:43,260 --> 00:10:44,550
I'll return it to her.

96
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:48,860
I'll personally apologize and say that I did something stupid out of curiosity.

97
00:10:48,860 --> 00:10:51,110
I'll return it to her.

98
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:55,620
So, give it to me.

99
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:01,580
I mean it!

100
00:11:01,580 --> 00:11:07,540
Just as you said, to the girl I like, and more than anything, to you, the friend I like...

101
00:11:07,540 --> 00:11:10,130
I don't want to do anything shameful.

102
00:11:19,870 --> 00:11:22,090
All right, I'll keep it a secret.

103
00:11:23,660 --> 00:11:26,350
I said I won't tell anyone.

104
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:32,970
I'll pretend I didn't see anything. So you better keep your promise.

105
00:11:40,870 --> 00:11:44,110
Thank you, my partner.

106
00:11:44,910 --> 00:11:46,400
Hee Seop!

107
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,060
Yeah.

108
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:52,340
Hello.

109
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:54,690
You're friends with our Hee Seop?

110
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:57,750
What's wrong?

111
00:12:03,437 --> 00:12:06,367

112
00:12:11,410 --> 00:12:15,040
 Yoo Beom Ryong is the one who stole Lee Joo Young's ring.

113
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:19,070
 The blue cap who ran away from the bridge that night was Baek Hee Seop.

114
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:22,100
 At the time, Baek Hee Seop had a companion.

115
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:26,510
 But Yoo Beom Ryong went in the same direction as the victim.

116
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:30,630
 Lee Joo Young's route...

117
00:12:32,350 --> 00:12:34,290

118
00:12:40,617 --> 00:12:42,707
 [Ilshin Photography

119
00:13:11,367 --> 00:13:18,887

120
00:13:24,787 --> 00:13:27,467

121
00:13:27,467 --> 00:13:29,667

122
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:36,420

123
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:46,400
 I said hurry up!

124
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,500
 Are you joking with me right now?

125
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:51,390
Go Min Soo?

126
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:56,640
 It really was unfair.

127
00:13:56,640 --> 00:14:01,610
 I wasn't even in Woojeong Village on the day of the incident.

128
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:06,750
 At the time, I was staying at a boarding school in the countryside.

129
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:11,200
 My mom sent me there to focus on my studies.

130
00:14:13,070 --> 00:14:16,750
 It was deep in the mountains where they didn't even have phones.

131
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:19,080
Do you want to die? Yeah?

132
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:21,230
Why is Go Min Soo...

133
00:14:26,090 --> 00:14:29,540
Come on!  If I ask you to give it to me,

134
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:32,380
you should quickly hand it over.

135
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:35,210
You talk too much, bitch.

136
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:39,430
Huh?

137
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:47,000
Is this your money? Huh?

138
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:51,310
You stole this from Mom's wallet anyway.

139
00:14:51,310 --> 00:14:53,300
Isn't that right?

140
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:55,130
Mi Sook.

141
00:14:58,060 --> 00:15:00,120
Pathetic loser.

142
00:15:01,580 --> 00:15:04,990
Mom kicked you out in the end.

143
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:08,410
What's with the bravado?

144
00:15:14,650 --> 00:15:16,630
Shit!

145
00:15:21,710 --> 00:15:23,510
Are you okay?

146
00:15:24,610 --> 00:15:25,980
Geez, seriously!

147
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:27,980
Damn it!

148
00:15:34,830 --> 00:15:38,420
Hey! Ow, it hurts!

149
00:15:38,420 --> 00:15:42,440
My arm, my arm! My arm, arm!

150
00:15:46,630 --> 00:15:50,090
I regret saving trash like you in the future!

151
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:51,330
What should I do with you?

152
00:15:51,330 --> 00:15:54,510
This is all because of you, asshole!

153
00:15:54,510 --> 00:15:57,260
- Because of you! 
 - Are you all right?

154
00:15:57,260 --> 00:16:00,780
Go to the nearest public phone and report it to the police.

155
00:16:00,780 --> 00:16:05,310
That place isn't that trustworthy, but we need to at least keep a damn record.

156
00:16:05,310 --> 00:16:09,690
I'll make sure he gets charged for his crime this time, no matter what.

157
00:16:09,690 --> 00:16:13,460
Go Mi Sook. Think very carefully.

158
00:16:18,670 --> 00:16:20,650
I don't want to...

159
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:23,940
report this.

160
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,780
I got my money back anyway.

161
00:16:38,980 --> 00:16:42,890
He'll return to the boarding school after blowing off some steam.

162
00:16:44,430 --> 00:16:46,260
That's enough.

163
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:50,750
If we have to deal with his troubles again,

164
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:53,450
my mom will kill me.

165
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:57,130
So...

166
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:04,190
I'd like to keep this between us.

167
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:20,907

168
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:30,020

169
00:17:38,727 --> 00:17:40,537

170
00:17:46,217 --> 00:17:48,467

171
00:17:48,470 --> 00:17:51,870
They're all driving me crazy, going around all over.

172
00:18:03,010 --> 00:18:05,880
 Lee Joo Young's movement tonight.

173
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:10,940
 One of the people in that vicinity has the highest probability of being the culprit.

174
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:16,600
 But all three suspects were there tonight.

175
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,800
All right, I'll keep it a secret.

176
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:25,960
I said I wouldn't tell anyone.

177
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:28,180

178
00:18:41,110 --> 00:18:42,730
All right.

179
00:18:42,730 --> 00:18:47,430
I'll return it. I'll apologize and I'll return it.

180
00:19:05,130 --> 00:19:08,210
I'll stay away from this neighborhood.

181
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:10,980
That's good, right?

182
00:19:10,997 --> 00:19:12,317

183
00:19:21,587 --> 00:19:25,197

184
00:19:25,197 --> 00:19:30,920
 Everyone there is telling their own lies.

185
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:38,020
 Why?

186
00:19:38,020 --> 00:19:40,127
 Exactly why?

187
00:19:40,127 --> 00:19:43,397

188
00:19:49,370 --> 00:19:51,920
Why aren't you saying anything?

189
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,690
The one with the blue cap.

190
00:19:57,490 --> 00:20:01,910
He's the one who might have killed my mom. You saw him, right?

191
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:12,510
Who was it? Was it someone we knew?

192
00:20:15,210 --> 00:20:18,290
I couldn't check.

193
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:21,950
I lost him like last time.

194
00:20:21,950 --> 00:20:24,600
It's my fault. I'm sorry.

195
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:30,980
You're lying.

196
00:20:33,060 --> 00:20:35,910
You said you didn't get hurt, but you did.

197
00:20:39,770 --> 00:20:42,580
- It must hurt every time your shirt... 
 - Oh, yeah.

198
00:20:42,580 --> 00:20:44,420
It's nothing.

199
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:48,910
How is Lee Joo Young?

200
00:20:51,110 --> 00:20:54,110
She seems a little nervous, but she's doing all right.

201
00:20:54,110 --> 00:20:58,380
She's worried that the police may catch on and follow her here.

202
00:20:58,380 --> 00:21:01,810
Then that'll get us in trouble, too.

203
00:21:01,810 --> 00:21:04,000
Don't worry.

204
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,670
No one will be able to come here tonight.

205
00:21:13,687 --> 00:21:15,757
 Yoon Young.

206
00:21:15,757 --> 00:21:17,707
 Yoon Young!

207
00:21:21,647 --> 00:21:24,017
Yoon Young!

208
00:21:29,247 --> 00:21:31,577
If you're going to whisper, then don't knock.

209
00:21:31,577 --> 00:21:34,007
If you're going to knock, then don't whisper.

210
00:21:34,007 --> 00:21:37,347
Shouldn't you decide on one strategy?

211
00:21:37,347 --> 00:21:42,507
I'm sorry at this late hour. Is Yoon Young here?

212
00:21:44,487 --> 00:21:48,157
Yoon Young! Are you all right?

213
00:21:48,157 --> 00:21:49,507
Me? Why?

214
00:21:49,507 --> 00:21:51,457
I heard everything from my dad!

215
00:21:51,457 --> 00:21:57,117
That there was a terrible incident involving a knife at the terminal.

216
00:21:57,117 --> 00:21:59,357
You must have been very scared.

217
00:21:59,357 --> 00:22:01,277
Oh, it's nothing.

218
00:22:01,277 --> 00:22:03,277
What do you mean, "nothing"?

219
00:22:04,277 --> 00:22:10,747
By any chance, are you planning to have Yoon Young sleep in the same place as the

220
00:22:10,747 --> 00:22:13,037
student teacher tonight?

221
00:22:13,037 --> 00:22:15,107
What?

222
00:22:15,107 --> 00:22:18,077
Oh, no.

223
00:22:18,077 --> 00:22:21,627
Then shall I have her sleep at my place? Just one night?

224
00:22:21,627 --> 00:22:25,627
Y-Yes. T-That would be good.

225
00:22:26,727 --> 00:22:29,987
Oh, I didn't think of that.

226
00:22:30,987 --> 00:22:32,587
You can go.

227
00:22:34,827 --> 00:22:38,447
No, it's all right. There was just some misunderstanding.

228
00:22:41,127 --> 00:22:44,347
Just take a break.

229
00:22:44,347 --> 00:22:46,397
Use that excuse.

230
00:22:47,267 --> 00:22:50,667
You said you came straight here after she passed away.

231
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:55,377
Even just for one night, stay by your mom's side.

232
00:22:55,377 --> 00:22:57,607
This is a good opportunity.

233
00:23:12,657 --> 00:23:24,357
♫  The loneliness below countless stars on a chilly night  ♫

234
00:23:25,807 --> 00:23:34,927
♫  No matter who I say it is, they would not understand this feeling  ♫

235
00:23:34,927 --> 00:23:39,267
♫  To you again  ♫

236
00:23:39,267 --> 00:23:41,327
Is my room a little messy?

237
00:23:41,327 --> 00:23:43,257
I try to keep it clean.

238
00:23:43,257 --> 00:23:45,987
But my mom scolds and slaps my back first.

239
00:23:45,987 --> 00:23:49,487
She even threatens to throw things out while I'm not here.

240
00:23:49,487 --> 00:23:52,317
Whoa. My mom was exactly the same way.

241
00:23:52,317 --> 00:23:54,207
Right?

242
00:23:54,207 --> 00:23:57,587
I don't know why all moms are like that.

243
00:23:58,547 --> 00:24:02,967
Even if I had a daughter one day, I would never do that to her.

244
00:24:04,467 --> 00:24:06,747
I'll go wash up. Make yourself comfortable.

245
00:24:06,747 --> 00:24:09,597
Okay, go wash up.

246
00:24:11,257 --> 00:24:20,787
♫  If you could tell me in some way that you love me  ♫

247
00:24:20,787 --> 00:24:23,847
♫  If you could  ♫

248
00:24:27,677 --> 00:24:32,297
No, it can't be. There's no way he would hide it from me.

249
00:24:46,027 --> 00:24:50,217
Who are you calling... at this time of night?

250
00:24:50,217 --> 00:24:53,147
I heard you were nervous all day?

251
00:24:53,147 --> 00:24:55,217
I'm checking the barricade.

252
00:24:56,727 --> 00:24:59,687

253
00:24:59,687 --> 00:25:02,437
 Why do you even need to check?

254
00:25:02,437 --> 00:25:06,227
I'm losing my mind here!

255
00:25:07,227 --> 00:25:08,547
Geez.

256
00:25:10,067 --> 00:25:12,487
Yes, everyone is gathered here.

257
00:25:12,487 --> 00:25:13,847
- Director Yoon. 
 - Wait a minute.

258
00:25:13,847 --> 00:25:15,737
What are you doing here? It's your turn.

259
00:25:15,737 --> 00:25:18,267
All right, all right.

260
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:20,427
Okay, wait just a bit.

261
00:25:20,427 --> 00:25:23,127
- Let's go, let's go. 
 - Applause! Applause!

262
00:25:26,177 --> 00:25:29,867
Director Yoon is singing! Big applause!

263
00:25:30,917 --> 00:25:34,777
No, no, no. I'll pass on singing.

264
00:25:34,777 --> 00:25:39,777
For those working hard for our crime-free village and peaceful Woojeong Village,

265
00:25:39,777 --> 00:25:43,687
the happiness of our policemen is all we need!

266
00:25:43,687 --> 00:25:45,957
Applause!

267
00:25:48,097 --> 00:25:53,237
As I mentioned, as our town's leader, tonight's dinner is on me!

268
00:25:53,237 --> 00:25:56,277
So, no one should think about going home tonight.

269
00:25:56,277 --> 00:26:02,217
- Eat and drink as much as you want, okay? 
  - Yes, yes!

270
00:26:02,217 --> 00:26:05,607
