A novel isn't a report.

535
00:46:43,047 --> 00:46:48,537
Just because it was based on real events doesn't mean she would write their real names.

536
00:46:48,537 --> 00:46:53,237
I didn't think Go Mi Sook's novel mentioned anything about a blue cap.

537
00:46:53,237 --> 00:46:56,937
But then, there was a similar character in her story.

538
00:46:57,637 --> 00:47:00,717
A man with blue hair.

539
00:47:00,717 --> 00:47:06,347
All this time I thought the "blue head" in this story was talking about blue hair.

540
00:47:06,347 --> 00:47:07,817
Ow!

541
00:47:11,197 --> 00:47:14,517
What happened, exactly?

542
00:47:14,517 --> 00:47:18,127
Do I need to tell you everything?

543
00:47:18,127 --> 00:47:21,897
Do I need to share every single thing that happens here?

544
00:47:21,897 --> 00:47:24,017
Do you do that?

545
00:47:24,017 --> 00:47:27,477
Were we even close enough to do that?

546
00:47:36,387 --> 00:47:38,590
You know, don't you?

547
00:47:42,087 --> 00:47:44,127
The one with the blue cap.

548
00:47:45,457 --> 00:47:48,167
You're not even curious to find out.

549
00:47:50,477 --> 00:47:52,807
You found out who it is.

550
00:47:53,507 --> 00:47:56,367
You didn't lose him at the cafe last night.

551
00:47:59,987 --> 00:48:04,227
You have no reason to tell me, but you don't have reasons to hide it from me, either. Why?

552
00:48:04,227 --> 00:48:08,397
- Why, exactly? 
 - I'll tell you since you seem to be mistaken.

553
00:48:08,397 --> 00:48:10,557
Think carefully.

554
00:48:10,557 --> 00:48:17,107
Do you think I'm here putting all in to chase criminals just to chase news?

555
00:48:17,107 --> 00:48:19,827
Because I feel sorry for the victims who died?

556
00:48:19,827 --> 00:48:22,477
The world is full of such tragedies.

557
00:48:22,477 --> 00:48:26,667
I don't have the time to go around rescuing all those people!

558
00:48:27,467 --> 00:48:29,587
Then, what's your reason?

559
00:48:32,997 --> 00:48:37,547
I'm a victim, also. I'm the fifth victim.

560
00:48:39,947 --> 00:48:42,857
Because they never caught the suspect here,

561
00:48:42,857 --> 00:48:45,847
I was going to die like your mom.

562
00:48:45,847 --> 00:48:48,037
That's why I'm here to save my life.

563
00:48:48,037 --> 00:48:51,727
Everything that happened in this town in 1987!

564
00:48:51,727 --> 00:48:56,067
I came here with all the data from newspapers, news broadcasts, and even police reports!

565
00:48:56,067 --> 00:49:00,497
But because of one little variable, now everything might change!

566
00:49:00,497 --> 00:49:04,237
Just thinking about that, I feel like my head will explode.

567
00:49:05,587 --> 00:49:07,767
But you know what?

568
00:49:09,327 --> 00:49:12,827
Do you know who the biggest variable is here?

569
00:49:14,677 --> 00:49:18,327
Is that why you sent me to my mom's last night?

570
00:49:20,277 --> 00:49:23,997
Because I shouldn't be curious about such variables,

571
00:49:24,654 --> 00:49:27,097
and don't interfere with anything.

572
00:49:27,097 --> 00:49:28,857
Just take a break...

573
00:49:30,347 --> 00:49:32,907
and stay out of your way.

574
00:49:36,367 --> 00:49:39,257
I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

575
00:49:40,005 --> 00:49:45,677
As long as I'm here, I can't sit here like an idiot and wait.

576
00:49:47,757 --> 00:49:50,287
If you don't want me to know, that's fine.

577
00:49:50,987 --> 00:49:53,577
I'll find out on my own.

578
00:49:55,060 --> 00:49:58,360

579
00:50:05,787 --> 00:50:08,707
I feel so uncomfortable here.

580
00:50:10,246 --> 00:50:13,527
What if Beom Ryong cries and tries to hold onto me?

581
00:50:13,527 --> 00:50:16,987
He said I'm the only one for him in this world.

582
00:50:18,377 --> 00:50:20,017
What are you doing?

583
00:50:20,837 --> 00:50:22,967
Hey, Baek Yoon Young.

584
00:50:29,207 --> 00:50:33,147
 The afternoon when the body of the first woman was discovered,

585
00:50:33,147 --> 00:50:37,677
 several suspicious scenes occurred in the town.

586
00:50:37,677 --> 00:50:42,677
 The man with the blue hair stood between the sun and the moon.

587
00:50:42,677 --> 00:50:48,877
 The man with the glasses didn't come out of the third stall for a long while.

588
00:50:48,877 --> 00:50:55,037
 The man who lost his memory didn't realize he was lying under the bridge.

589
00:51:01,937 --> 00:51:06,027
 Since today is the day they would've discovered Lee Joo Young dead,

590
00:51:06,027 --> 00:51:09,357
 this will take place this afternoon.

591
00:51:09,357 --> 00:51:13,987
 If the blue-haired man really means the blue cap, then...

592
00:51:17,647 --> 00:51:20,727
what would be between the sun and the moon?

593
00:51:20,727 --> 00:51:22,567
I don't know.

594
00:51:22,567 --> 00:51:24,167
What is this?

595
00:51:24,167 --> 00:51:26,107
It's scary.

596
00:51:28,687 --> 00:51:31,607
Just go see Yoo Beom Ryong.

597
00:51:31,607 --> 00:51:34,587
It's something you should experience at least once.

598
00:51:35,667 --> 00:51:38,097
All right.

599
00:51:41,407 --> 00:51:44,947
But don't hang out with anyone who writes that kind of story.

600
00:51:48,277 --> 00:51:49,737
I don't like it.

601
00:51:49,737 --> 00:51:52,147
How do you know I didn't write it?

602
00:51:52,147 --> 00:51:53,727
Are you an idiot?

603
00:51:53,727 --> 00:51:56,377
If you wrote it, you'd know what it means.

604
00:51:56,377 --> 00:51:58,177
Whoever wrote it would know.

605
00:51:58,177 --> 00:52:01,477
Since they chose each word carefully.

606
00:52:04,617 --> 00:52:06,757
I'll be back.

607
00:52:19,567 --> 00:52:23,267
There's no way she would know what was written 30 years later.

608
00:53:26,977 --> 00:53:28,867
 Hae Joon!

609
00:53:28,867 --> 00:53:30,527
 Hae Joon!

610
00:53:30,527 --> 00:53:32,747
 Hey, Hae Joon!

611
00:53:59,637 --> 00:54:04,378

612
00:54:06,867 --> 00:54:09,778

613
00:55:03,577 --> 00:55:06,177
I heard the Korean language teacher got hurt...

614
00:55:08,417 --> 00:55:10,947
Let me know if you need any help.

615
00:55:10,947 --> 00:55:15,127
I like what you've done so far.

616
00:55:15,127 --> 00:55:20,507
So, you liked what happened to Go Min Soo.

617
00:55:27,777 --> 00:55:31,657
A man stood between the sun and the moon vacantly.

618
00:55:37,247 --> 00:55:40,147
If there's a sentence like that,

619
00:55:40,147 --> 00:55:43,417
what could "between the sun and moon" mean?

620
00:55:49,787 --> 00:55:52,117
How would I know?

621
00:55:59,307 --> 00:56:01,757
I shouldn't have asked.

622
00:56:02,917 --> 00:56:05,557
Isn't that the name of the record store?

623
00:56:09,928 --> 00:56:13,268

624
00:56:16,248 --> 00:56:19,247

625
00:56:20,147 --> 00:56:22,487

626
00:56:23,497 --> 00:56:26,898

627
00:56:38,907 --> 00:56:45,198

628
00:57:08,477 --> 00:57:14,018

629
00:57:54,327 --> 00:57:57,417
Do you know what time it is right now?

630
00:58:01,427 --> 00:58:07,577
Then, do you know what it feels like waiting for someone who skipped school?

631
00:58:08,517 --> 00:58:13,317
I can't even make phone calls in this damn year of 1987.

632
00:58:19,617 --> 00:58:21,597
I'm sorry.

633
00:58:23,107 --> 00:58:28,047
I knew I had to tell you, but I decided on my own and kept it to myself.

634
00:58:28,047 --> 00:58:31,837
But that's not why I sent you to her house last night.

635
00:58:32,657 --> 00:58:34,437
I know.

636
00:58:36,917 --> 00:58:39,407
The one with the blue cap is your—

637
00:58:39,407 --> 00:58:41,507
I know that, too.

638
00:58:43,927 --> 00:58:46,917
I saw him myself.

639
00:58:46,917 --> 00:58:51,627
I think I understand why you kept it from me.

640
00:58:52,807 --> 00:58:54,967
Because he's my family.

641
00:58:56,387 --> 00:58:59,377
He's just one of the suspects.

642
00:59:03,547 --> 00:59:06,187
I did hate him, but...

643
00:59:06,187 --> 00:59:10,147
I didn't ever think he was that kind of person.

644
00:59:10,887 --> 00:59:14,587
He's someone my dad thinks of dearly.

645
00:59:16,467 --> 00:59:18,467
Even more than us.

646
00:59:20,917 --> 00:59:22,757
What did you say?

647
00:59:24,497 --> 00:59:26,147
Excuse me?

648
00:59:28,927 --> 00:59:31,497
Who are you talking about right now?

649
00:59:31,497 --> 00:59:34,127
Weren't you talking about the one with the blue cap?

650
00:59:34,127 --> 00:59:35,837
Yes, that's right.

651
00:59:35,837 --> 00:59:40,427
So why would Baek Hee Seop think so dearly of himself...

652
00:59:42,647 --> 00:59:46,727
Are you saying the one with the blue cap is my dad?

653
00:59:50,117 --> 00:59:52,707
Who did you see, then?

654
00:59:54,508 --> 00:59:58,278

655
01:00:22,118 --> 01:00:25,498

656
01:00:27,207 --> 01:00:29,837
I saw my uncle, my dad's older brother.

657
01:00:29,837 --> 01:00:32,177
Baek Yoo Seop.

658
01:00:32,177 --> 01:00:34,897
Baek Yoo Seop wasn't even a suspect at the time.

659
01:00:34,897 --> 01:00:38,087
And he wasn't even in the vicinity last night...

660
01:00:53,097 --> 01:00:55,817
Now it makes sense.

661
01:01:09,637 --> 01:01:12,237

662
01:01:12,237 --> 01:01:15,397

663
01:01:15,397 --> 01:01:17,147
Brother!

664
01:01:17,847 --> 01:01:20,317
What are you doing here? It's not even the weekend.

665
01:01:20,317 --> 01:01:23,667
I was supposed to meet someone but looks like they didn't come. You?

666
01:01:23,667 --> 01:01:25,897
I'm just meeting someone.

667
01:01:25,897 --> 01:01:28,827
- Shall we go inside and talk? 
 - No, it's stuffy in there.

668
01:01:28,827 --> 01:01:31,217
If you won't be long, I'll wait in front.

669
01:01:31,217 --> 01:01:32,407
Oh, really?

670
01:01:32,407 --> 01:01:35,027
That would be great!

671
01:01:37,577 --> 01:01:40,567
Wow, it looks cool, Brother.

672
01:01:49,657 --> 01:01:52,107
Here.

673
01:01:52,107 --> 01:01:53,477
Let's see.

674
01:01:53,477 --> 01:01:55,657
Looking good!

675
01:01:55,657 --> 01:01:58,987
It suits me, right?

676
01:01:58,987 --> 01:02:01,887
- Don't take too long! 
 - Okay, Brother.

677
01:02:07,368 --> 01:02:14,358

678
01:02:32,537 --> 01:02:35,167
♫  I found the meaning of life  ♫

679
01:02:35,167 --> 01:02:38,047
♫  Come to me, darling  ♫

